          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">A</hi>RE the guests of this house still doom'd to be cheated?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-2" n="2">Sure the fates have decreed they by halves should be treated.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-3" n="3">In the day of good John<note place="foot">Â·Dr John Stearne, late Lord Bishop of Clogher, who had been the predecessor of Dr Swift in the deanery of St Patrick's, and was always distinguished for his great hospitality.</note>, if you came here to dine,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-4" n="4">You had choice of good meat, no choice of good wine.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-5" n="5">In Jonathan's reign, if you come here to eat,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-6" n="6">You have choice of good wine, no choice of good meat.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-7" n="7">Oh Jove! then how fully might all sides be blest,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-8" n="8">Wouldst thou but agree to this humble request:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-9" n="9">Put both deans in one; or if that's too much trouble,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-07E2-line-10" n="10">Instead of the deans, make the dean'ry double.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
